install prisma
npm install prisma @prisma/client

initial Prisma
npx prisma init --datasource-provider postgresql 


setup postgres
docker run --name my-postgres -e POSTGRES_USER=workflow_user -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=password -e POSTGRES_DB=app_db -p 5432:5432 -d postgres:16

setup pgadmin
docker run -p 5050:80 -e PGADMIN_DEFAULT_EMAIL=abhisek.das@gmail.com -e PGADMIN_DEFAULT_PASSWORD=admin --name pgadmin -d dpage/pgadmin4

Open localhost:5050
email : abhisek.das@gmail.com // Same email which was used in pgadmin setup
password : password // Same password which was used to setup pgadmin

Add a server
General : 
  name : :"Local Postgres"
Connection:
  host : host.docker.internal
  port : 5432 // Same port used in postgres setup
  username : workflow_user // Same username used in postgres setup
  password : password // Same password used in postgres setup


Change the .env
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://workflow_user:password@localhost:5432/app_db?schema=public"

each and evertime you make any change to Model , you need to migrate
npx prisma migrate dev --name init
npx prisma generate


### Generate Permission Seeds
npm install -D tsx typescript
npx prisma db seed
